$TER &quot;Headquartered in North Reading, MA, Teradyne designs, develops, manufactures and sells automated test equipment and robotics products. Its automatic test systems are used to test semiconductors, wireless products, data storage and complex electronics systems in consumer electronics, wireless, automotive, industrial, computing, communications, and aerospace and defense industries. 
: Despite reported record Q1 results with 70% of revenue tied to AI, the stock has surged roughly 23% in the last month. Investors are now locking in profits before the expected &quot;digestion period&quot; in the second half of the year. 
Average Price Target: Approximately $375.19 to $382.73 (Consensus). High Estimate: $470.00 to $493.50&quot;

$TER --Teradyne Keeps Quarterly Dividend at $O.13 per Share;
Payable June 12 to Holders of Record as of May 21
